- Each scenario tries up to N=3 times with the same prompt
- If ANY of the 3 attempts has the expected substrings, PASS
- If ALL 3 attempts miss, FAIL (the block reason really isn't reaching the model)
- Log every attempt's full output to artifacts even on PASS, so we can see the model's variation envelope
- Wait 1s between retries (avoid rate-limit hits)

**Set `--turn-budget 3` (or equivalent) so the test fails fast if the model spirals trying to find a workaround.**

**Cross-test-run determinism:** model output varies. Run each assertion as a substring-or check (e.g., contains "blocked" OR "denied" OR "rejected"). If all three miss, fail. Document this as known-flaky-on-model-version-changes; if a future model version changes vocabulary materially we'll need to update.

**Acceptance:** at least one test asserts the model's final message contains the rule id; a second test asserts it contains the command verbatim; a third asserts the model abandoned the destructive task rather than finding a workaround. Retry envelope is exercised: the test_helper logs N attempts even on first-try success, so we can see flakiness patterns.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T23:56:05.142676468Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T08:42:39.204721331Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["codex","coverage","e2e"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"git_safety_guard-ovw4.4.4","depends_on_id":"git_safety_guard-ovw4.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-27T23:56:05.142676468Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"git_safety_guard-ovw4.4.4","depends_on_id":"git_safety_guard-ovw4.4.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-27T23:56:05.142676468Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
